'''花园口广场'''（Plaza San Lorenzo Ruiz）<ref name="sunstar">{{cite news | author=Managbanag, Nicole C. | title=A Binondo adventure | url=http://www.sunstar.com.ph/cagayan-de-oro/feature/2012/05/05/binondo-adventure-219917 | work=Sun.Star Cagayan de Oro | publisher=Sun.Star Publishing, Inc. | archiveurl=https://archive.is/20140107145831/http://www.sunstar.com.ph/cagayan-de-oro/feature/2012/05/05/binondo-adventure-219917 | date=2012-05-05 | archivedate=2014-01-07 | accessdate=2013-07-11 | deadurl=yes }}</ref> 是[[马尼拉|马尼拉]][[岷伦洛区|岷伦洛区]]的主要广场。广场上的[[岷伦洛教堂|李乐伦圣殿]]（岷伦洛教堂）是马尼拉市的主要教堂之一，被认为是岷伦洛区的中心。

该广场最初称为岷伦洛广场，后来更名为[[卡洛斯四世|卡洛斯四世]]广场，再更名为卡尔德隆·德·拉·巴尔卡广场（得名于西班牙剧作家[[佩德罗·卡尔德隆·德·拉·巴尔卡|佩德罗·卡尔德隆·德·拉·巴尔卡]]）<ref name="megaworld">{{cite web | title=Manila Day | url=http://megaworldlifestylemalls.com/main/blog/page/0/39/Manila-Day | work=Megaworld Lifestyle Malls | publisher=Megaworld Corporation | date=2013-06-24 | accessdate=2013-07-04 | deadurl=yes | archiveurl=https://archive.is/20130704104235/http://megaworldlifestylemalls.com/main/blog/page/0/39/Manila-Day | archivedate=2013-07-04 }}</ref>。这次更名若非出自时任总督，就是出自当时管理岷伦洛教堂的道明会神父<ref name="alcazaren">{{cite news | author=Alcazaren, Paulo | title=Plaza Lorenzo ruins?: We need a miracle to save Plaza Lorenzo Ruiz | url=http://www.philstar.com/modern-living/158788/plaza-lorenzo-ruins-we-need-miracle-save-plaza-lorenzo-ruiz | work=The Philippine Star | publisher=PhilStar Daily, Inc. | date=2002-04-27 | accessdate=2013-07-04 | archive-date=2017-01-03 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170103013545/http://www.philstar.com/modern-living/158788/plaza-lorenzo-ruins-we-need-miracle-save-plaza-lorenzo-ruiz | dead-url=no }}</ref>。1981年9月12日，该广场改为现名，得名于在日本殉道的菲律宾第一位殉道圣人[[李乐伦|李乐伦]]<ref name="BP">Republic of the Philippines. (Enacted: September 12, 1981). [http://www.chanrobles.com/bataspambansa/bataspambansablg133.html Batas Pambansa Blg. 133 - An Act to Rename Plaza Calderon de la Barca and the San Fernando Bridge, Both Located in Binondo, Manila, as Plaza Lorenzo Ruiz and Lorenzo Ruiz Bridge, Respectively, In Honor of the Filipino Proto-martyr] {{Wayback|url=http://www.chanrobles.com/bataspambansa/bataspambansablg133.html |date=20131027140159 }}.  Retrieved July 4, 2013 from the Chan Robles Virtual Law Library.</ref>。

